msgid "Default: not selected"
msgstr "Privzeto: ni izbrano"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1778
#, no-c-format
msgid "Minimal SMB protocol version:"
msgstr "Najmanjša različica protokola SMB:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1781 index.docbook:1816
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following protocol versions can be set:"
msgstr "Nastavite lahko naslednje različice protokola:"

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1785 index.docbook:1820
#, no-c-format
msgid "NT1 (Classic CIFS/SMBv1 protocol)"
msgstr "NT1 (klasični protokol CIFS/SMBv1)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1788 index.docbook:1823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the classic version of the protocol. It is used by &Windows; NT and "
"is known as CIFS or SMBv1. It is considered to be unsafe and was disabled in "
"the latest &Samba; and &Windows; versions."
msgstr ""
"To je trenutno klasična različica protokola. Uporablja ga &Windows; NT in je "
"znan kot CIFS ali SMBv1. Smatra se, da ni varen in je bil onemogočen v "
"zadnji različici &Samba; in različici &Windows;."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1793 index.docbook:1828
#, no-c-format
msgid "SMB2 (Windows Vista and above)"
msgstr "SMB2 (Windows Vista in novejši)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1796 index.docbook:1831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the re-implementation of the SMB protocol. It is used by &Windows; "
"Vista and above."
msgstr ""
"To je ponovna implementacija protokola SMB. Uporablja ga &Windows; Vista in "
"višje."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1801 index.docbook:1836
#, no-c-format
msgid "SMB3 (Windows 8 and above)"
msgstr "SMB3 (Windows 8 in novejši)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1804
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the SMBv3 protocol version. It features several improvements of the "
"functionality and performance of SMBv2 as well as several security "
"enhancements. This protocol version is used by &Windows; 8 and above."
msgstr ""
"To je različica protokola SMBv3. Vsebuje več strežniških izboljšav "
"funkcionalnosti in zmogljivosti SMBv2 kot tudi več strežniških varnostnih "
"izboljšav. To različico protokola uporablja &Windows; 8 in novejši."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1808
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: <guimenuitem>SMB2 (Windows Vista and above)</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "Privzeto: <guimenuitem>SMB2 (Windows Vista in novejši)</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1813
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximal SMB protocol version:"
msgstr "Največja različica protokola SMB:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the SMBv3 protocol version. It features serveral improvements of the "
"functionality and performance of SMBv2 as well as serveral security "
"enhancements. This protocol version is used by &Windows; 8 and above."
msgstr ""
"To je različica protokola SMBv3. Vsebuje več strežniških izboljšav "
"funkcionalnosti in zmogljivosti SMBv2 ter več strežniških varnostnih "
"izboljšav. To različico protokola uporablja &Windows; 8 in novejši."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1843
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: <guimenuitem>SMB3 (Windows 8 and above)</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "Privzeto: <guimenuitem>SMB3 (Windows 8 in novejši)</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1853 index.docbook:2039 index.docbook:3259
#, no-c-format
msgid "Behavior"
msgstr "Vedenje"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1858
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect printer shares"
msgstr "Zaznaj skupni tiskalnik"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1861
#, no-c-format
msgid "Printer shares are detected."
msgstr "Zaznani skupni tiskalniki."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1867
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect hidden shares"
msgstr "Zaznaj skrite skupne vire"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1870
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Hidden shares are detected. Hidden shares are ending with a $ sign, &eg; "
"Musik$ or IPC$."
msgstr ""
"Zaznane so skriti skupni diski. Skriti diski se končajo z znakom $, &eg; "
"Musik$ ali IPC$."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preview hidden files and directories"
msgstr "Predogled skritih datotek in imenikov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Show all files and directories including the hidden ones when opening a "
"share's contents in the preview dialog."
msgstr ""
"Pri odpiranju vsebine skupne rabe v pogovornem oknu za predogled prikaži vse "
"datoteke in imenike, vključno s skritimi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1892
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advanced Settings"
msgstr "Napredne nastavitve"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1895
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Samba</title>"
msgstr "<title>Samba</title>"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1900
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the SMB port to"
msgstr "Nastavite vrata SMB na"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enabling this setting sets the remote SMB port number to communicate with a "
"remote host to the value defined in the spin box. Under BSD, this is also "
"the port that is used for mounting."
msgstr ""
"Če omogočite to nastavitev, se nastavi številka vrat oddaljenega SMB za "
"komunikacijo z oddaljenim gostiteljem na vrednost, določeno v vrtilnem "
"polju. Pod BSD so to tudi vrata, ki se uporabljajo za namestitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1904
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unless you are using a firewall or have a customized network setup, you do "
"not need to change anything here."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj vam ni treba ničesar spreminjati, razen če uporabljate požarni zid ali "
"imate prilagojeno nastavitev omrežja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1905
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: 139"
msgstr "Privzeto: 139"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1910
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the encryption level to"
msgstr "Nastavi raven šifriranja na"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1913
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the level of encryption that is used to make connections. The following "
"settings can be chosen:"
msgstr ""
"Nastavi raven šifriranja, ki se uporablja za vzpostavljanje povezav. "
"Izberete lahko naslednje nastavitve:"

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1917
#, no-c-format
msgid "None"
msgstr "Noben"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1920
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption is not used."
msgstr "Šifriranje se ne uporablja."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1925
#, no-c-format
msgid "Request"
msgstr "Zahtevek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1928
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption is requested."
msgstr "Zahtevano je šifriranje."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:1933
#, no-c-format
msgid "Require"
msgstr "Zahtevaj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1936
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption is required."
msgstr "Zahtevano je šifriranje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1940
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: <guimenuitem>None</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "Privzeto: <guimenuitem>Brez</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1945
#, no-c-format
msgid "This computer is on a large network neighborhood"
msgstr "Ta računalnik je v veliki omrežni soseščini"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1948
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the default configuration, all available master browsers are queried when "
"the browse list is compiled. On large network neighborhoods this can be very "
"time consuming. Enabling this setting restricts the query to three master "
"browsers."
msgstr ""
"V privzeti konfiguraciji so vsi razpoložljivi glavni brskalniki poizvedeni, "
"ko je sestavljen seznam brskanja. V velikih omrežnih soseščinah je to lahko "
"zelo zamudno. Če omogočite to nastavitev, omejite poizvedbo na tri glavne "
"brskalnike."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1954
#, no-c-format
msgid "Master browsers require authentication"
msgstr "Glavni brskalniki zahtevajo avtentikacijo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1957
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the workgroup master browsers require authentication to return the browse "
"list, you need to check this button. This may be the case for example with "
"some NAS devices. This setting is rarely needed and might even cause a "
"master browser to return an empty browse list."
msgstr ""
"Če glavni brskalniki delovne skupine zahtevajo avtentikacijo za vrnitev "
"seznama za brskanje, morate potrditi ta gumb. To lahko velja na primer za "
"nekatere naprave NAS. Ta nastavitev je redko potrebna in lahko celo "
"povzroči, da glavni brskalnik vrne prazen seznam za brskanje."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1963
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Kerberos for authentication"
msgstr "Za avtentikacijo uporabite Kerberos"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1966
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Kerberos for authentication in an Active Directory environment."
msgstr "Uporabite Kerberos za avtentikacijo v okolju Active Directory."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1972
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Winbind ccache for authentication"
msgstr "Za avtentikacijo uporabite predpomnilnik Winbind"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1975
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try to use the credentials cached by Winbind."
msgstr "Poskusi uporabiti poverilnice, ki jih predpomni Winbind."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1982
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wake-On-LAN"
msgstr "Wake-On-LAN"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1984
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To be able to use the Wake-On-LAN capability of &smb4k;, you have to enable "
"this setting. The hosts that should to be woken up have to be defined "
"through the <link linkend="
"\"network_neighborhood_browser_defining_custom_settings\">custom settings "
"editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite uporabljati zmožnost Wake-On-LAN &smb4k;, morate omogočiti to "
"nastavitev. Gostitelje, ki jih je treba prebuditi, je treba določiti v <link "
"linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser_defining_custom_settings"
"\">urejevalniku nastavitev po meri</link>."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:1989
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable Wake-On-LAN features"
msgstr "Omogoči funkcije Wake-On-LAN"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1992
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable Wake-on-LAN (WOL) features. Wake-On-LAN is an ethernet computer "
"networking standard that allows a computer to be turned on or woken up by a "
"network message. Smb4K uses a magic packet send via a UDP socket to wake up "
"remote servers. If you want to take advantage of the Wake-On-LAN feature, "
"you need to enable this option."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči funkcije Wake-on-LAN (WOL). Wake-On-LAN je ethernetni standard "
"računalniškega omrežja, ki omogoča vklop ali prebujanje računalnika z "
"omrežnim sporočilom. Smb4K uporablja čarobni paket, poslan prek vtičnice "
"UDP, da prebudi oddaljene strežnike. Če želite izkoristiti funkcijo Wake-On-"
"LAN, morate to možnost omogočiti."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1997
#, no-c-format
msgid "Waiting time"
msgstr "Čas čakanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2000
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the waiting time in seconds between the sending of the magic Wake-On-"
"LAN packets and the scanning of the network neighborhood or the mounting of "
"a share."
msgstr ""
"To je čakalni čas v sekundah med pošiljanjem čarobnih paketov Wake-On-LAN in "
"skeniranjem omrežne soseščine ali priklopom skupnih virov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2001
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: 5 s"
msgstr "Privzeto: 5 s"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2017
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting"
msgstr "Priklapljanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2019
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This configuration page contains all settings regarding the mounting of "
"shares. The settings appearing here are depending on the operation system "
"you are using."
msgstr ""
"Ta konfiguracijska stran vsebuje vse nastavitve v zvezi s priklopom skupnih "
"virov. Tukaj prikazane nastavitve so odvisne od operacijskega sistema, ki ga "
"uporabljate."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:2022
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the \"Mounting\" configuration page"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona konfiguracijske strani \"Priklapljanje\""

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:2025
#, no-c-format
msgid "The \"Mounting\" configuration page"
msgstr "Konfiguracijska stran \"Priklapljanje\""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2036
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The settings in this tab are the same for all supported operating systems."
msgstr "Nastavitve v tem zavihku so enake za vse podprte operacijske sisteme."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2044
#, no-c-format
msgid "Remount shares"
msgstr "Ponovno priklopi skupne vire"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Remount all your shares that were mounted when you exited the program or "
"changed a profile. If the remounting of a share fails, Smb4K will retry the "
"next time it is started. Shares that were mounted by other users are ignored."
msgstr ""
"Ponovno namestite vse svoje skupne vire, ki so bili priklopljeni, ko ste "
"zapustili program ali spremenili profil. Če ponovna namestitev skupnih virov "
"ne uspe, bo Smb4K znova poskusil ob naslednjem zagonu. Skupni viri, ki so "
"jih priklopili drugi uporabniki, so prezrti."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2052
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of remount attempts"
msgstr "Število poskusov ponovnega priklopa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2055
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set the number of attempts that are made to remount shares before Smb4K "
"gives up."
msgstr ""
"Nastavite število poskusov ponovnega priklopa skupnih virov, preden Smb4K "
"odneha."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2056
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: 1"
msgstr "Privzeto: 1"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:2061
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interval between remount attempts"
msgstr "Interval med poskusi ponovnega priklopa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2064
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the time that elapses between attempts to remount shares."
msgstr ""
"Nastavite čas, ki preteče med poskusi ponovnega priklopa skupnih virov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2065
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: 5 min"
msgstr "Privzeto: 5 min"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2073
#, no-c-format
msgid "Unmount all personal shares on exit"
msgstr "Odklopi vse osebne skupne vire ob izhodu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2076
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unmount all shares that belong to you when the program exits. Shares that "
"are owned by other users are ignored."
msgstr ""
"Odklopi vse skupne vire, ki vam pripadajo, ko se program zapre. Skupni viri, "
"ki so v lasti drugih uporabnikov, so prezrti."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2082
#, no-c-format
msgid "Force unmounting of inaccessible shares"
msgstr "Prisilni odklop nedostopnih skupnih virov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2085
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Force unmounting of inaccessible shares (&Linux; only). In case a share is "
"inaccessible, a lazy unmount is performed. Before the actual unmounting is "
"done, a warning dialog is shown asking to approve the unmount."
msgstr ""
"Vsili odklop nedostopnih skupnih virov (samo &Linux;). V primeru, da je "
"skupni vir nedostopen, se izvede leni odklop. Preden je dejanski odklop "
"končan, se prikaže pogovorno okno z opozorilom, ki zahteva odobritev odklopa."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2091
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detect all shares that are mounted on the system"
msgstr "Zaznaj vse skupne vire, ki so priklopljeni v sistemu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2094
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will not only see the shares that were mounted and are owned by you, but "
"also all other mounts using the SMBFS (BSD) and &CIFS; (&Linux;) file system "
"that are present on the system."
msgstr ""
"Ne boste videli samo skupnih virov, ki so bile priklopljeni in so v vaši "
"lasti, ampak tudi vse druge priklope z uporabo SMBFS (BSD) in &CIFS; "
"(&Linux;), ki so prisotni v sistemu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common Mount Settings (&Linux; only)"
msgstr "Skupne nastavitve priklopa (samo &Linux;)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Common Mount Settings</guilabel> tab is only available under "
"&Linux; and the listed options refer to the <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> / <ulink url=\"man:/mount."
"smb3\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.smb3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> command. The settings present under BSD "
"can be found in the <link linkend="
"\"configuration_page_mounting_mount_settings\">Mount Settings (BSD only)</"
"link> section."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek <guilabel>Skupne nastavitve priklopa</guilabel> je na voljo samo pod "
"&Linux; in navedene možnosti se nanašajo na <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> / <ulink url=\"man:/mount."
"smb3\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.smb3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> ukaz. Nastavitve v BSD najdete v razdelku "
"<link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_mount_settings\">Nastavitve "
"priklopa (samo BSD)</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2112 index.docbook:2686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Common Options"
msgstr "Običajne možnosti"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Write access"
msgstr "Dostop za pisanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The write access to a share can be determined here. This option is "
"independent of the file mask and the folder mask settings above. Available "
"options are:"
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko določite pisalni dostop do skupnega diska. Ta možnost je "
"neodvisna od maske datoteke in zgornjih nastavitev maske mape. Razpoložljive "
"možnosti so:"

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2124
#, no-c-format
msgid "read-write"
msgstr "branje-pisanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>rw</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>rw</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount the share read-write."
msgstr "Priklopi skupni vir za branje in pisanje."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2133
#, no-c-format
msgid "read-only"
msgstr "samo za branje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>ro</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>ro</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount the share read-only."
msgstr "Priklopi skupni vir samo za branje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2141
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: not selected; <guimenuitem>read-write</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "Privzeto: ni izbrano; <guimenuitem>branje-pisanje</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2146 index.docbook:2741
#, no-c-format
msgid "Client character set"
msgstr "Nabor znakov odjemalca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>iocharset=CHARSET</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>iocharset=CHARSET</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2150
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the character set used by the client side (&ie; your computer) to one "
"of the following:"
msgstr ""
"Nastavi nabor znakov, ki ga uporablja stran odjemalca (tj. vaš računalnik) "
"na eno od naslednjega:"

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2154 index.docbook:2748 index.docbook:2943
#, no-c-format
msgid "default"
msgstr "privzeto"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default character set used by the client's kernel. In this case the "
"<option>iocharset</option> option is omitted from the command line."
msgstr ""
"Privzeti nabor znakov, ki ga uporablja odjemalčevo jedro. V tem primeru je "
"možnost <option>iocharset</option> izpuščena v ukazni vrstici."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2162 index.docbook:2756
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-1"
msgstr "iso8859-1"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2165 index.docbook:2759
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-1:1998. This character-encoding scheme is used throughout the "
"Americas, Western Europe, Oceania, and much of Africa."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-1:1998. Ta shema kodiranja znakov se uporablja po vsej Ameriki, "
"Zahodni Evropi, Oceaniji in večjem delu Afrike."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2170 index.docbook:2764
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-2"
msgstr "iso8859-2"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2173 index.docbook:2767
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-2:1999. It is informally referred to as \"Latin-2\". It is "
"generally intended for Central or \"Eastern European\" languages that are "
"written in the Latin script."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-2:1999. Neuradno se imenuje \"Latin-2\". Na splošno je namenjen "
"srednje- ali \"vzhodnoevropskim\" jezikom, ki so zapisani v latinični pisavi."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2178 index.docbook:2772
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-3"
msgstr "iso8859-3"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2181 index.docbook:2775
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-3:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-3 or South "
"European. It was designed to cover Turkish, Maltese and Esperanto, though "
"the introduction of ISO/IEC 8859-9 superseded it for Turkish."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-3:1999. Neuradno se imenuje latinsko-3 ali južnoevropsko. "
"Zasnovan je bil za turščino, malteščino in esperanto, čeprav ga je uvedba "
"standarda ISO/IEC 8859-9 nadomestila za turščino."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2186 index.docbook:2780
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-4"
msgstr "iso8859-4"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2189 index.docbook:2783
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-4:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-4 or North "
"European. It was designed to cover Estonian, Latvian, Lithuanian, "
"Greenlandic, and Sami. It has been largely superseded by ISO/IEC 8859-10 and "
"Unicode."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-4:1998. Neuradno se imenuje Latin-4 ali Severnoevropski. "
"Zasnovan je bil za pokrivanje estonskega, latvijskega, litovskega, "
"grenlandskega in samskega jezika. V veliki meri sta ga nadomestila ISO/IEC "
"8859-10 in Unicode."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2194 index.docbook:2788
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-5"
msgstr "iso8859-5"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2197 index.docbook:2791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-5:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Cyrillic. It was "
"designed to cover languages using a Cyrillic alphabet such as Bulgarian, "
"Belarusian, Russian, Serbian and Macedonian but was never widely used."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-5:1999. Neuradno se imenuje latinica/cirilica. Zasnovan je bil "
"za pokrivanje jezikov, ki uporabljajo cirilico, kot so bolgarščina, "
"beloruščina, ruščina, srbščina in makedonščina, vendar ni bil nikoli široko "
"uporabljen."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2202 index.docbook:2796
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-6"
msgstr "iso8859-6"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2205 index.docbook:2799
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-6:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Arabic. It was "
"designed to cover Arabic."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-6:1999. Neuradno se imenuje latinščina/arabščina. Zasnovan je "
"bil za pokrivanje arabščine."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2210 index.docbook:2804
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-7"
msgstr "iso8859-7"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2213 index.docbook:2807
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-7:2003. It is informally referred to as Latin/Greek. It was "
"designed to cover the modern Greek language."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-7:2003. Neuradno se imenuje latinščina/grščina. Zasnovan je bil "
"tako, da pokriva sodobni grški jezik."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2218 index.docbook:2812
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-8"
msgstr "iso8859-8"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2221 index.docbook:2815
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-8:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin/Hebrew. ISO/IEC "
"8859-8 covers all the Hebrew letters, but no Hebrew vowel signs."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-8:1999. Neuradno se imenuje latinščina/hebrejščina. ISO/IEC "
"8859-8 zajema vse hebrejske črke, vendar ne hebrejskih znakov samoglasnikov."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2226 index.docbook:2820
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-9"
msgstr "iso8859-9"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2229 index.docbook:2823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-9:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-5 or Turkish. It "
"was designed to cover the Turkish language, designed as being of more use "
"than the ISO/IEC 8859-3 encoding."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-9:1999. Neuradno se imenuje latinščina-5 ali turščina. Zasnovan "
"je bil za pokrivanje turškega jezika, zasnovan tako, da je bolj uporaben kot "
"kodiranje ISO/IEC 8859-3."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2234 index.docbook:2828
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-13"
msgstr "iso8859-13"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2237 index.docbook:2831
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-13:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-7 or Baltic Rim. "
"It was designed to cover the Baltic languages, and added characters used in "
"the Polish language missing from the earlier encodings ISO 8859-4 and ISO "
"8859-10. Unlike these two, it does not cover the Nordic languages."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-13:1998. Neuradno se imenuje Latin-7 ali Baltic Rim. Zasnovan "
"je bil za pokrivanje baltskih jezikov in je dodal znake, uporabljene v "
"poljskem jeziku, ki manjkajo v prejšnjih kodiranjih ISO 8859-4 in ISO "
"8859-10. Za razliko od teh dveh ne pokriva nordijskih jezikov."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2242 index.docbook:2836
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-14"
msgstr "iso8859-14"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2245 index.docbook:2839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-14:1998. It is informally referred to as Latin-8 or Celtic. It "
"was designed to cover the Celtic languages, such as Irish, Manx, Scottish "
"Gaelic, Welsh, Cornish, and Breton."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-14:1998. Neuradno se imenuje latinsko-8 ali keltsko. Zasnovan "
"je bil tako, da pokriva keltske jezike, kot so irščina, manski jezik, "
"škotska galščina, valižanščina, korniščina in bretonščina."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2250 index.docbook:2844
#, no-c-format
msgid "iso8859-15"
msgstr "iso8859-15"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2253 index.docbook:2847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-15:1999. It is informally referred to as Latin-9 (and for a "
"while Latin-0). It is similar to ISO 8859-1, and thus also intended for "
"“Western European” languages, but replaces some less common symbols with the "
"euro sign and some letters that were deemed necessary."
msgstr ""
"ISO/IEC 8859-15:1999. Neuradno se imenuje Latin-9 (in nekaj časa Latin-0). "
"Je podoben standardu ISO 8859-1 in tako namenjen tudi »zahodnoevropskim« "
"jezikom, vendar nadomešča nekatere manj pogoste simbole z znakom evra in "
"nekaterimi črkami, ki so se zdele potrebne."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2258 index.docbook:2852
#, no-c-format
msgid "utf8"
msgstr "utf8"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2261 index.docbook:2855
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unicode (or Universal Coded Character Set) Transformation Format – 8-bit. "
"UTF-8 is used by many &Linux; distributions as default character set, and "
"is, in addition, by far the most common encoding for the World Wide Web."
msgstr ""
"Format pretvorbe Unicode (ali univerzalni kodirani nabor znakov) – 8-bitni. "
"UTF-8 uporablja veliko &Linux; distribucije kot privzeti nabor znakov, poleg "
"tega pa je daleč najpogostejše kodiranje za svetovni splet."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2266 index.docbook:2860
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-r"
msgstr "koi8-r"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2269 index.docbook:2863
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-R (RFC 1489) is an 8-bit character encoding, derived from the KOI-8 "
"encoding by the programmer Andrei Chernov in 1993 and designed to cover "
"Russian, which uses a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""
"KOI8-R (RFC 1489) je 8-bitno kodiranje znakov, ki izhaja iz kodiranja KOI-8 "
"programerja Andreja Černova leta 1993 in je zasnovano za pokrivanje ruščine, "
"ki uporablja cirilico."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2274 index.docbook:2868
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-u"
msgstr "koi8-u"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2277 index.docbook:2871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-U (RFC 2319) is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover "
"Ukrainian, which uses a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""
"KOI8-U (RFC 2319) je 8-bitno kodiranje znakov, zasnovano za pokrivanje "
"ukrajinščine, ki uporablja cirilico."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2282 index.docbook:2876
#, no-c-format
msgid "koi8-ru"
msgstr "koi8-ru"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2285 index.docbook:2879
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KOI8-RU is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover Russian, "
"Ukrainian, and Belarusian which use a Cyrillic alphabet."
msgstr ""
"KOI8-RU je 8-bitno kodiranje znakov, zasnovano za rusko, ukrajinsko in "
"belorusko abecedo, ki uporabljajo cirilico."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2290 index.docbook:2884 index.docbook:3135
#, no-c-format
msgid "cp1251"
msgstr "cp1251"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2293 index.docbook:2887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Windows-1251 is an 8-bit character encoding, designed to cover languages "
"that use the Cyrillic script such as Russian, Bulgarian, Serbian Cyrillic "
"and other languages. In Linux, the encoding is known as cp1251."
msgstr ""
"Windows-1251 je 8-bitno kodiranje znakov, zasnovano za jezike, ki "
"uporabljajo cirilico, kot so ruska, bolgarska, srbska cirilica in drugi "
"jeziki. V Linuxu je kodiranje znano kot cp1251."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2298 index.docbook:2892
#, no-c-format
msgid "gb2312"
msgstr "gb2312"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2301 index.docbook:2895
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"GB/T 2312-1980 is a key official character set of the People's Republic of "
"China, used for Simplified Chinese characters. GB2312 is the registered "
"internet name for EUC-CN, which is its usual encoded form. GB/T 2312-1980 "
"has been superseded by GBK and GB18030, which include additional characters, "
"but GB/T 2312 remains in widespread use as a subset of those encodings."
msgstr ""
"GB/T 2312-1980 je ključni uradni nabor znakov Ljudske republike Kitajske, ki "
"se uporablja za poenostavljene kitajske znake. GB2312 je registrirano "
"internetno ime za EUC-CN, ki je njegova običajna kodirana oblika. GB/T "
"2312-1980 sta nadomestila GBK in GB18030, ki vključujeta dodatne znake, "
"vendar GB/T 2312 ostaja v široki uporabi kot podnabor teh kodiranj."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2306 index.docbook:2900
#, no-c-format
msgid "big5"
msgstr "big5"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2309 index.docbook:2903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Big-5 or Big5 is a Chinese character encoding method used in Taiwan, Hong "
"Kong, and Macau for traditional Chinese characters. The People's Republic of "
"China (PRC), which uses simplified Chinese characters, uses the GB 18030 "
"character set instead."
msgstr ""
"Big-5 ali Big5 je metoda kodiranja kitajskih znakov, ki se uporablja v "
"Tajvanu, Hong Kongu in Macau za tradicionalne kitajske znake. Ljudska "
"republika Kitajska (LRK), ki uporablja poenostavljene kitajske znake, "
"namesto tega uporablja nabor znakov GB 18030."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2314 index.docbook:2908
#, no-c-format
msgid "euc-jp"
msgstr "euc-jp"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2317 index.docbook:2911
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"EUC-JP is a variable-width encoding used to represent the elements of three "
"Japanese character set standards, namely JIS X 0208, JIS X 0212, and JIS X "
"0201."
msgstr ""
"EUC-JP je kodiranje s spremenljivo širino, ki se uporablja za predstavitev "
"elementov treh japonskih standardov za nabor znakov, in sicer JIS X 0208, "
"JIS X 0212 in JIS X 0201."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2322 index.docbook:2916
#, no-c-format
msgid "euc-kr"
msgstr "euk-kr"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2325 index.docbook:2919
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"EUC-KR is a variable-width encoding to represent Korean text using two coded "
"character sets, KS X 1001 (formerly KS C 5601) and either ISO 646:KR (KS X "
"1003, formerly KS C 5636) or US-ASCII, depending on variant. KS X 2901 "
"(formerly KS C 5861) stipulates the encoding and RFC 1557 dubbed it as EUC-"
"KR."
msgstr ""
"EUC-KR je kodiranje s spremenljivo širino za predstavitev korejskega "
"besedila z uporabo dveh kodiranih naborov znakov, KS X 1001 (prej KS C 5601) "
"in ISO 646:KR (KS X 1003, prej KS C 5636) ali US-ASCII, odvisno na varianto. "
"KS X 2901 (prej KS C 5861) določa kodiranje, RFC 1557 pa ga je poimenoval "
"EUC-KR."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:2330 index.docbook:2924
#, no-c-format
msgid "tis-620"
msgstr "tis-620"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2333 index.docbook:2927
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Thai Industrial Standard 620-2533, commonly referred to as TIS-620, is the "
"most common character set and character encoding for the Thai language."
msgstr ""
"Tajski industrijski standard 620-2533, običajno imenovan TIS-620, je "
"najpogostejši nabor znakov in kodiranje znakov za tajski jezik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: not selected; CHARSET: <guimenuitem>default</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "Privzeto: ni izbrano; CHARSET: <guimenuitem>privzeto</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2344
#, no-c-format
msgid "&CIFS; Unix Extensions Support"
msgstr "&CIFS; Podpora za razširitve Unix"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2348
#, no-c-format
msgid "All or most of the servers support the &CIFS; Unix extensions"
msgstr "Vsi ali večina strežnikov podpira &CIFS; Unix razširitve"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2351
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: none"
msgstr "Možnost: brez"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most versions of &Samba; support the &CIFS; Unix or POSIX extensions. For "
"these servers, some options are not needed, because the right values are "
"negotiated during the mount process. For other servers, you might want to "
"uncheck this option, so that predefined values can be passed to the server. "
"Please note that if your computer is located in a &Windows; dominated "
"network neighborhood with only a few &Samba; servers, you can safely uncheck "
"this option and define custom settings for the &Samba; servers."
msgstr ""
"Večina različic &Samba; podpira &CIFS; Razširitve Unix ali POSIX. Za te "
"strežnike nekatere možnosti niso potrebne, ker se prave vrednosti izpogajajo "
"med postopkom priklopa. Za druge strežnike boste morda želeli počistiti to "
"možnost, tako da se vnaprej določene vrednosti lahko posredujejo strežniku. "
"Upoštevajte, da če se vaš računalnik nahaja v oknu &Windows; prevladujoča "
"omrežna soseščina z le nekaj &Samba; lahko varno počistite to možnost in "
"določite nastavitve po meri za &Samba; strežnike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2353
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case you uncheck this option, consider to switch on permission checks "
"under <link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_advanced_mount_settings"
"\">Advanced Mount Settings</link>."
msgstr ""
"Če počistite to možnost, razmislite o vklopu preverjanja dovoljenj pod <link "
"linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_advanced_mount_settings\">Napredne "
"nastavitve priklopa</link>."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2359 index.docbook:2691
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the user and group ID"
msgstr "Nastavi ID uporabnika in skupine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2362
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options: <option>uid=UID</option> and <option>gid=GID</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>uid=UID</option> in <option>gid=GID</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2363 index.docbook:2695
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smb4k; uses your user and group ID for mounting if this setting is enabled. "
"They are displayed here for information purposes only and cannot be changed."
msgstr ""
"Če je ta nastavitev omogočena, &smb4k; za priklop uporabi vaš ID uporabnika "
"in skupine. Prikazana sta tukaj samo v informativne namene in ju ni mogoče "
"spremeniti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2364 index.docbook:2375 index.docbook:2386 index.docbook:2696
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the support for the &CIFS; Unix extensions is selected, this setting "
"is disabled."
msgstr ""
"V primeru, da je podpora za &CIFS; Izbrane so razširitve Unix, ta nastavitev "
"je onemogočena."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2365 index.docbook:2697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: selected; UID: your UID, GID: your GID"
msgstr "Privzeto: izbrano; UID: vaš UID, GID: vaš GID"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2370 index.docbook:2705
#, no-c-format
msgid "File mode"
msgstr "Datotečni način"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2373
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>file_mode=MODE</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>file_mode=MODE</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the permissions that are applied to files. The value is given in octal "
"and may have 3 or 4 digits. The SUID, SGID and sticky bit are not allowed. "
"To learn more about the file mode (file_mode), you should read the <ulink "
"url=\"man:/mount(8)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> and <ulink url="
"\"man:/umask(2)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>umask</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>2</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> manual pages."
msgstr ""
"Določi dovoljenja, ki veljajo za datoteke. Vrednost je podana v osmiškem "
"sistemu in ima lahko 3 ali 4 števke. SUID, SGID in lepljivi bit niso "
"dovoljeni. Če želite izvedeti več o načinu datoteke (file_mode), preberite "
"strani priročnika <ulink url=\"man:/"
"mount(8)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> in <ulink url=\"man:/"
"umask(2)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>umask</refentrytitle><manvolnum>2</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2376 index.docbook:2387
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default: selected; ARG: 0755"
msgstr "Privzeto: izbrano; ARG: 0755"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2381 index.docbook:2715
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directory mode"
msgstr "Imeniški način"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2384
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>dir_mode=MODE</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>dir_mode=MODE</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sets the permissions that are applied to directories. The value is given in "
"octal and may have 3 or 4 digits. The SUID, SGID and sticky bit are not "
"allowed. To learn more about the directory mode (dir_mode), you should read "
"the <ulink url=\"man:/mount(8)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> and <ulink url="
"\"man:/umask(2)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>umask</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>2</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> manual pages."
msgstr ""
"Nastavi dovoljenja, ki veljajo za imenike. Vrednost je podana v osmiškem "
"sistemu in ima lahko 3 ali 4 števke. SUID, SGID in lepljivi bit niso "
"dovoljeni. Če želite izvedeti več o načinu imenika (dir_mode), preberite "
"strani priročnika <ulink url=\"man:/"
"mount(8)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> and <ulink url=\"man:/"
"umask(2)\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>umask</refentrytitle><manvolnum>2</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:2399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Advanced Mount Settings (&Linux; only)"
msgstr "Napredne nastavitve priklopa (samo &Linux;)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2401
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Advanced Mount Settings</guilabel> tab is only available under "
"&Linux; and the listed options refer to the <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> / <ulink url=\"man:/mount."
"smb3\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.smb3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> command. The settings present under BSD "
"can be found in the <link linkend="
"\"configuration_page_mounting_mount_settings\">Mount Settings (BSD only)</"
"link> section."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek <guilabel>Napredne nastavitve priklopa</guilabel> je na voljo samo "
"pod &Linux; in navedene možnosti se nanašajo na <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> / <ulink url=\"man:/mount."
"smb3\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.smb3</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> ukaz. Nastavitve v BSD najdete v razdelku "
"<link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_mount_settings\">Nastavitve "
"priklopa (samo BSD)</link>."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2405
#, no-c-format
msgid "Definitely assign the UID"
msgstr "Vsekakor dodeli UID"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>forceuid</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>forceuid</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instruct the client (i.e. your side) to ignore any user ID (UID) provided by "
"the server for files and directories and to always assign the owner to be "
"the value of the transmitted UID."
msgstr ""
"Odjemalcu (tj. vaši strani) naročite, naj ignorira vse uporabniške ID-je "
"(UID), ki jih posreduje strežnik za datoteke in imenike, in naj vedno dodeli "
"lastnika vrednosti poslanega UID-ja."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2415
#, no-c-format
msgid "Definitely assign the GID"
msgstr "Vsekakor dodeli GID"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2418
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>forcegid</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>forcegid</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2419
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instruct the client (i.e. your side) to ignore any group ID (GID) provided "
"by the server for files and directories and to always assign the owner to be "
"the value of the transmitted GID."
msgstr ""
"Odjemalcu (tj. vaši strani) naročite, naj prezre vse ID skupine (GID), ki "
"jih posreduje strežnik za datoteke in imenike, in naj vedno dodeli lastnika "
"vrednosti poslanega GID."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2425
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do permission checks"
msgstr "Opravi preverjanje dovoljenj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2428
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>perm</option> or <option>noperm</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>perm</option> ali <option>noperm</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2429
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The client side checks if you have the correct UID and GID to manipulate "
"files and directories on the share. This is in addition to the normal ACL "
"check on the target machine done by the server software. You most definitely "
"want to switch this feature off, if the server(s) support the &CIFS; Unix "
"extensions and you are, hence, not allowed to fully access the share."
msgstr ""
"Stran odjemalca preveri, ali imate pravilen UID in GID za manipulacijo "
"datotek in imenikov v skupni rabi. To je poleg običajnega preverjanja ACL na "
"ciljnem računalniku, ki ga izvaja strežniška programska oprema. To funkcijo "
"zagotovo želite izklopiti, če strežnik(-i) podpirajo &CIFS; Razširitve Unix "
"in vam zato ni dovoljen popoln dostop do skupnega diska."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2435
#, no-c-format
msgid "Attempt to set UID and GID"
msgstr "Poskusi nastaviti UID in GID"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2438
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>setuids</option> or <option>nosetuids</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>setuids</option> ali <option>nosetuids</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the &CIFS; Unix extensions are negotiated with the server the client side "
"will attempt to set the effective UID and GID of the local process on newly "
"created files, directories, and devices. If this feature is turned off, the "
"default UID and GID defined for the share will be used. It is recommended "
"that you read the manual page of <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> before you change this setting."
msgstr ""
"Če se &CIFS; razširitve Unix dogovorijo s strežnikom, stran odjemalca pa bo "
"poskušala nastaviti učinkovit UID in GID lokalnega procesa na novo "
"ustvarjenih datotekah, imenikih in napravah. Če je ta funkcija izklopljena, "
"bosta uporabljena privzeti UID in GID, definirana za skupni disk. "
"Priporočamo, da preberete priročnik za <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> preden spremenite to nastavitev."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2445
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use server inode numbers"
msgstr "Uporabite številke inode strežnika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2448
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>serverino</option> or <option>noserverino</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>serverino</option> ali <option>noserverino</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2449
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use inode numbers (unique persistent file identifiers) returned by the "
"server instead of automatically generating temporary inode numbers on the "
"client side. This parameter has no effect if the server does not support "
"returning inode numbers or similar. It is recommended that you read the "
"manual page of <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> before you change this setting."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite številke inode (edinstvene obstojne identifikatorje datotek), ki "
"jih vrne strežnik, namesto samodejnega generiranja začasnih številk inode na "
"strani odjemalca. Ta parameter nima učinka, če strežnik ne podpira vračanja "
"številk inode ali podobnega. Priporočamo, da preberete priročnik za <ulink "
"url=\"man:/mount.cifs\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> preden "
"spremenite to nastavitev."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Translate reserved characters"
msgstr "Prevedite rezervirane znake"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>mapchars</option> or <option>nomapchars</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>mapchars</option> ali <option>nomapchars</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Translate six of the seven reserved characters (not backslash, but including "
"the colon, question mark, pipe, asterisk, greater than, and less than "
"characters) to the remap range (above 0xF000), which also allows the client "
"side to recognize files created with such characters by &Windows;’s POSIX "
"emulation. This can also be useful when mounting to most versions of "
"&Samba;. This has no effect if the server does not support Unicode."
msgstr ""
"Prevedi šest od sedmih rezerviranih znakov (ne poševnice nazaj, ampak "
"vključno z dvopičjem, vprašajem, navpično črto, zvezdico, znaki, večjimi od "
"in manjšimi od) v obseg ponovne preslikave (nad 0xF000), kar tudi omogoča "
"strani odjemalca, da prepozna ustvarjene datoteke s takimi znaki z &Windows; "
"emulacijo POSIX. To je lahko koristno tudi pri priklopu na večino različic "
"&Samba;. To nima učinka, če strežnik ne podpira Unicode."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2465
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not send byte range lock requests"
msgstr "Ne pošiljajte zahtev za zaklepanje obsega bajtov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2468
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>nobrl</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>nobrl</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2469
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not send byte range lock requests to the server. This is necessary for "
"certain applications that break with cifs style mandatory byte range locks "
"(and most cifs servers do not yet support requesting advisory byte range "
"locks)."
msgstr ""
"Strežniku ne pošiljajte zahtev za zaklepanje obsega bajtov. To je potrebno "
"za nekatere aplikacije, ki prekinejo obvezno zaklepanje obsega bajtov v "
"slogu cifs (in večina strežnikov cifs še ne podpira zahtevanja svetovalnih "
"zaklepov obsega bajtov)."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2475
#, no-c-format
msgid "SMB protocol version"
msgstr "Različica protokola SMB"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option: <option>vers=VERS</option>"
msgstr "Možnost: <option>vers=VERS</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define which version of the SMB protocol is to be used. Normally, this "
"option does not need to be enabled because the protocol version is "
"negotiated between the client and the server."
msgstr ""
"Določite, katera različica protokola SMB bo uporabljena. Običajno te "
"možnosti ni treba omogočiti, ker se o različici protokola pogajata odjemalec "
"in strežnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2480 index.docbook:2559
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following values are allowed:"
msgstr "Dovoljene so naslednje vrednosti:"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2484
#, no-c-format
msgid "1.0 (Classic &CIFS;/SMBv1 protocol)"
msgstr "1.0 (klasični protokol &CIFS;/SMBv1)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This causes <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> to use the classic &CIFS;/SMBv1 protocol."
msgstr ""
"To povzroči, da <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> uporablja klasični &CIFS; /SMBv1 protokol."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:2492
#, no-c-format
msgid "2.0 (Windows Vista SP1/Windows Server 2008)"
msgstr "2.0 (Windows Vista SP1/Windows Server 2008)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:2495
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This causes <ulink url=\"man:/mount.cifs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount.cifs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> to use the SMBv2.002 protocol. This was "
